name: Psychoanalytic Electronic Publishing (PEP)
description: Contains the complete text and illustrations of 51 premier journals in psychoanalysis, 96 classic psychoanalytic books, and the full text and Editorial notes of the 24 volumes of the Standard Edition of the Complete Psychological Works of Sigmund Freud as well as the 18 volume German Freud Standard Edition Gesammelte Werke. It spans over 142 publication years and contains the full text of articles whose source ranges from 1871 through 2013. There are over 90 thousand articles and over 11 thousand figures and illustrations that originally resided on over 1720 volumes with over 880 thousand printed pages.
